<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,649,999]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,793,819]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
I have examined the male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[810,908,793,819]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[966,1129,793,820]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">four paratypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Makhan (HNHM)" authorityName="Makhan (HNHM" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pietersenae">
<emphasis box="[1170,1335,794,819]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">H. pietersenae</emphasis>
Makhan (HNHM)
</taxonomicName>
. All 
<specimenCount box="[315,484,829,855]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
have the form of the distal piece as illustrated herein (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1203,829,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–43" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[177,1428,185,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-15@73.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 42–43. Habitus and male genitalia. 42. Hydrochus astrictus Perkins. 43. Hydrochus pietersenae Makhan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5043328" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5043328/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
). The male genitalia drawing in 
<bibRefCitation author="Makhan, D." box="[279,455,865,891]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="389 - 393" refId="ref50546" refString="Makhan, D. (2001) A new genus, Soesilius, and a new species of Hydrochidae (Coleoptera) from America. Russian Entomological Journal, 10, 389 - 393." type="journal article" year="2001">Makhan (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, which does not include two of the three processes of the distal piece, is inaccurate and misleading. Images of the male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[678,776,901,927]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
are given herein. The 
<typeStatus box="[1024,1122,901,927]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
is in poor condition, broken due to the poor specimen technique of a prior worker. Therefore, a different specimen, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1270,937,963]" name="Bolivia" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, has been used for the habitus images.
</paragraph>
